This is held in the collection of the National Maritime Museum in Greenwich . The medal , which featured busts of Admirals John Jellicoe and David Beatty , was produced in response to a competition conceived by Sir Arthur Evans for a medal to commemorate the Battle of Jutland of 1916 . Gilbert designed the obverse around the busts of Admirals Jellicoe and Beatty and the reverse is by Charles Wheeler . Gilbert 's medal came third . The Royal Numismatic Society arranged for the three winning models to be struck in bronze"], ["Welbeck Abbey", "Welbeck , Nottinghamshire", "In around 1926 and working with Weingartner , Gilbert executed two wall plaques for the chapel of Welbeck Abbey near Worksop .
